- Packages/com.vtuber-system-base.core-ipc-foundation/Tests/Editor/ClientSessionManagerTests.cs
    Nine NUnit tests under VTuberSystemBase.CoreIpc.Tests.Editor.
    Uses two private fakes (FakeTransport implementing
    ITransportAdapter, FakeClientConnection implementing
    IClientConnection) so the tests stay in the Tests.Editor
    asmdef without depending on Tests.Runtime/TestSupport.

    The four scenarios mandated by tasks.md §3.3:
        Scenario1_ConnectSucceeds_TransitionsToConnected
            One queued success → state log
            [Connecting, Connected]; backoff.AttemptCount = 0
            (reset on connect).
        Scenario2_DropAfterConnected_RecoversThroughReconnecting
            Two queued successes; SimulateDrop on the first
            connection → state log
            [Connecting, Connected, Reconnecting,
             Connecting, Connected]; old connection disposed;
            ConnectAttemptCount = 2; backoff reset on second
            success.
        Scenario3_AttemptsExceedMax_TransitionsToPermanentlyDisconnected
            One success + maxAttempts (=3) failures → state log
            [Connecting, Connected, Reconnecting,
             PermanentlyDisconnected]; ConnectAttemptCount =
            1 + maxAttempts; backoff.ExceededMaxAttempts true.
        Scenario4_ShutdownDuringReconnect_StopsRetriesAndCleanlyDisconnects
            One success + 100 queued failures, with a delay
            function that never returns until ct cancels.
            Drop, wait for Reconnecting, call ShutdownAsync().
            Asserts state == Disconnected, ShutdownRequested,
            and ConnectAttemptCount unchanged (no retries fired
            after shutdown).

    Additional coverage:
        ReceivedFrames_AreForwardedToCallback
            FakeClientConnection.PushFrame(...) drains through the
            receive loop and the onMessageReceived callback in FIFO
            order.
        Constructor_NullTransport_Throws
        Constructor_NullStateMachine_Throws
        Constructor_NullBackoff_Throws
            Argument-null validation per parameter.
        StartAsync_CalledTwice_Throws
            Second StartAsync invocation throws
            InvalidOperationException.

    Test infrastructure:
        - InstantDelay() : returns Task.CompletedTask immediately so
          backoff math runs without real sleeps.
        - NeverReturningDelay() : returns a TaskCompletionSource that
          only completes via cancellation; used to pin the worker
          inside the reconnect delay so the shutdown test can verify
          it preempts pending retries.
        - WaitForAsync(predicate, timeout, description) : polls the
          predicate every 10 ms with a 5 s default timeout; this
          avoids the StateChanged-event race window that briefly
          appears between SimulateDrop() and the worker's transition
          to Reconnecting.
        - AttachStateLog(sm, sync) : subscribes a thread-safe log
          before StartAsync so every transition is captured for the
          end-of-test sequence assertion.

