Implementation summary:
- ClientSessionManager closes the loop opened by tasks 3.1 and 3.2:
  ConnectionStateMachine owns the FSM, ReconnectBackoff owns the
  retry schedule, and ClientSessionManager composes both with
  ITransportAdapter to drive a single client session through its
  full lifecycle (connect → receive → drop → reconnect → permanent
  failure or shutdown).
- The class is pure C# on the existing
  VTuberSystemBase.CoreIpc.Core asmdef. No Unity engine references,
  so it runs in EditMode tests directly without PlayerLoop pumping.
- Per Req 5.4 the *Publish* path on Bus is responsible for the
  NotConnected error during disconnects; ClientSessionManager only
  drives state and forwards inbound frames, leaving send-side
  precheck to CoreIpcBus (already implemented in task 2.5).
- The injected delay function and the optional
  onMessageReceived/log callbacks make the class fully unit-testable
  without spinning a real WebSocket. Task 4.5 will plug in
  WebSocketTransportAdapter; task 7.1 will plug in the codec/queue.

